All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Admin
An Admin or Cinema Staff which has access to the system Have the rights to Create/Update/Delete movie listing, showtimes or configure system settings
AdminController
This class represents the Controller for Admin It handles all database functions related to Admin database file
AdminView
This class represents the Admin View when using Admin Module
BookedSeatView
This class represents when the MovieGoer and selected a seat and showned the booked seat view with the details and information of the Movie and Price
Cast
A Cast represents the actor/actress which belongs to a Movie a cast contains an integer ID, it's name and the corresponding Movie it belongs to.
CastController
This class represents the Controller for Cast It handles all database functions related to Cast database file
Cinema
A Cinema which belongs to a Cineplex.
CinemaClass
Enum CinemaClass to represent the class of Cinema
CinemaController
This class represents the Controller for Cinema It handles all database functions related to Cinema database file
CinemaShowTime
A CinemaShowTime belongs to a Cinema with attributes of Cinema Code, Hall number, Cineplex, CinemaClass to represent the Class(Standard/Platinum), Showtimes of this cinema, which may have many showtimes in this cinema and SeatingLayout (The static representaion in text file)
CinemaShowTimeController
This class represents the Controller for CinemaShowTime It handles all database functions related to CinemaShowTime database file
Cineplex
A Cineplex which consists of at least 3 or more Cinemas with attributes of Cineplex Code, Cineplex Name, Cineplex located mall, Cineplex's address, Cineplex's distinct mall location e.g Level 5 West Mall Cineplex's nearest MRT station, and a list of Cinemas belonging in this Cineplex
CineplexController
This class represents the Controller for CineplexController It handles all database functions related to CineplexController database file
ConfigureSystemSettingView
This class represents Configure System Setting View which is used by an Admin to change the ticket prices or adding a Holidayv
Constants
This class represents the static constant for strings for readability and reusability
CURMovieListingView
This class represents the view for Admin when Create/Update/Remove movie listing is selected and Admin wishes to make changes to the corresponding information
CURShowTimeView
This class represents the view for Admin when Create/Update/Remove CinemaShowTime is selected and Admin wishes to make changes to the corresponding information
DatabaseController
This class represents the Controller for Database, containing misc functions like generating or ID
EnterReviewView
This class represents the view for MovieGoer To enter a review to a Movie
ExploreCineplexesView
This class represents the view when MovieGoer selects to view a List of All Cineplex
ListTop5View
This class represents the view for MovieGoer to list the top 5 Movie Either by ticket sales or movie review which the options will be enabled or disabled by Admin
LoginView
This class represents the view for User to Login, which is used when authenticated an Admin or a MovieGoer
MainMoblimApp
This is the Main Moblim App that will be the first executed
Movie
A Movie that is shown in the Cinemas, A movie can be in many Cinemas
MovieClassifiedRating
Enum MovieClassifiedRating to represent the Film Rating of the movie which restricts the age regarding the maturity of content
MovieController
This class represents the Controller for Movie It handles all database functions related to Movie database file
MovieGoer
A MovieGoer who utilized the system to View Movies/Cineplex/Cinemas or Booking a ticket for a Movie Usually has restricted access, a guest must register as a MovieGoer to be able to book a ticket.
MovieGoerController
This class represents the Controller for MovieGoer It handles all database functions related to MovieGoer database file
MovieGoerView
This class represents the view for MovieGoer To View Movies or Cineplex or its own transaction history Only authenticated MovieGoer can view its transaction history
MovieShowingStatus
Enum MovieShowingStatus to represent the status of the Movie End of Show means that MovieGoer won't be able to view or book that movie
MovieShowTimeView
This class represents the view for MovieGoer when they selected a to Login, which is used when authenticated an Admin or a MovieGoer
MovieType
Enum MovieShowingStatus to represent the Type of the Movie 2D is the standard while 3D is the elevated experience and more expensive
RegisterView
This class represents the view for User to Register and new account, it can be an Admin or a MovieGoer
Review
A Review that represents the MovieGoer's description about his experience of the movie.
ReviewController
This class represents the Controller for Review It handles all database functions related to Review database file
SearchListMoviesView
This class the View when User selected Explore Movies option A list of options will be available for User to further select
Seat
A Seat that belongs to a Seating Layout.
SeatingLayout
A Seating Layout that shows the Seats of the Cinema A moviegoer will be shown this layout while booking for a Movie of a specific CinemaShowTime
SeatingLayoutController
This class represents the Controller for SeatingLayout It handles all database functions related to SeatingLayout database file
SeatSelectionView
This class represents when the MovieGoer selected a ShowTimeID and will be brought to see the Seating Layout of the CinemaShowTime
SystemSettingController
This class represents the Controller for SeatingLayout that corresponds to a CinemaShowTime It handles all database functions related to SeatingLayout database file
Ticket
A Ticket that a belongs to a Transaction Can be booked by MovieGoer that corresponds to the Seat ID in the CinemaShowTime
TicketController
This class represents the Controller for Ticket that corresponds to a Transaction It handles all database functions related to Ticket database file
TicketDay
Enum TicketDay to represent the movie day of the Ticket which is used to add charges if it's weekend
TicketPriceController
This class represents the Controller for Ticket Pricing It handles all database functions related to System Settings database file
TicketType
Enum TicketType to represent the type of the Ticket which differentiate the age group of the movie goer
Transaction
 
TransactionController
This class represents the Controller for Transaction It handles all database functions related to Transaction database file
TransactionHistoryView
This class represents the view when MovieGoer is authenticated and selects to view it's transaction history
TransactionView
This class represents the view for MovieGoer when User Confirms the Booked Seat, will be shown the Transaction details made.
User
A base class for Admin or MovieGoer It consists of the username and password and similar attributes
UserInputValidationController
 
UserSession
 
ViewMovieDetailView
This class represents the view for MovieGoer selects a Movie and will be shown all the description of Movie attributes
